FBIS4-14222 "drnes082_l_94017" FBIS-NES-94-082 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 ISRAEL Settler Receives Life for Murdering `Terrorist' Settler Receives Life for Murdering `Terrorist' TA2804075194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 28 Apr 94 TA2804075194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] The Jerusalem District Court sentenced Yoram Skolnik, from the settlement of Ma'ale Hever in the Hebron Hills, to life in prison. He was convicted of the premeditated murder of the terrorist Musa Sabah, whose hands and feet were bound after he was apprehended for having stabbed a settler near the settlement of Susya in the Hebron Hills.
